<subSubSection id="512E1C1E65D7384834EBBC9DC3AC6033" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8158B06380B1549B0F63C860076E539B" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE573DDED4EA9047BED404FE347F2C75" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName id="3673A573424F56E15435214E5EADBFF0" authorityName="K. Hori &amp; Khine" authorityYear="2022" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Thylacopteris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thylacopteris minuta" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="C5050D0424841AE1ABB1233372B5DEBE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Thylacopteris minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C3A94A8AA35D2C17D0A7A3E24C4DF2E4" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. papillosa" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillosa">
<emphasis id="EDC152930CBF67D6068C6CFA590E28BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">T. papillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 20-40 sclerenchyma strands per rhizome in cross-section. However, 
<taxonomicName id="5415BEB79241D7BFBB68F98769AC111D" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. minuta" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="23269DC6F9D5C6F8C7A242295F72C517" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">T. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="06A53C38665A95A6DB6F8965D1759ACD" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. papillosa" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillosa">
<emphasis id="BD6F45BEE19DABEB9588E86B88292033" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">T. papillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with sori shallowly sunken vs. 
<taxonomicName id="F268782D0F2F3FD66F9F6DB87C859CAB" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. papillosa" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillosa">
<emphasis id="2E611F63255E8E24ED3CEE9F85CE2A91" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">T. papillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sori deeply sunken. In addition, the lamina of 
<taxonomicName id="200777862B7719D405DE65D97F95AD54" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. minuta" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="6D86AE1E3994D5EFD80476A7D5B6D3E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">T. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a maximal length of 15 cm vs. a maximal length of 59 cm in 
<taxonomicName id="C844C4F76D2864E5E733395865E743B0" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. papillosa" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillosa">
<emphasis id="09679584FABF726B9645D03D575BBF3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">T. papillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="576E87E8CA7C3D4F98DD0C0828EFE650" authorityName="K. Hori &amp; Khine" authorityYear="2022" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Thylacopteris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thylacopteris minuta" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="5DC8CC0D2F279892BF62E4C5E0C5B021" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Thylacopteris minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from the New Guinea endemic 
<taxonomicName id="B5E0FC69FBFE409AF270231644F8B3D4" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. diaphana" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diaphana">
<emphasis id="6EDD0EC1B5AD2B38568FF41D4FF530B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">T. diaphana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which lacks sclerenchyma strands in the rhizome, has superficial sori, and lamina with a maximal length of 45 cm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
